ted 04-24-2002).]</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aariis_Stasis_Prexus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">/Bump!<P>Thx on info !!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shaylah</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, I do not agree that anyone should ever do RF first.  That is just bad form, when there are so many clerics out there on all servers who are at this stage (and have done the parts in order).<BR>It does not "fill up your inventory for months" - if you are doing the items in order, you have the first orb for a while, then you have the sceptre/note/message, which gets you the second orb and the swirling or shimmering pearl - only 3 slots taken up.<BR>I agree wholeheartedly about VI messing this thing up - by making RF a "FFA" camp as I heard one GM call it - they have cheapened our EPIC.  I for one think every one of us, cleric and other classes alike, should write a feedback note to VI (a polite one, so we can at least maintain some sort of respect) stating our feelings.<BR>Yes, Ragefire would be a MUCH better spawn if his trigger was fixed - what other classes have to wait up to 3 (or more) days after a turn-in for thir mob to show up? (there might be, I am not up to date on everyone's epics)<P>ok I have had my rant.  If any of you really really want VI to know how we feel, write a feedback note to them.  Remember, the squeaky wheel gets the grease, and it is high time we started sqeaking about this!<p>[This message has been edited by Shaylah (edited 05-13-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cland</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shameless Bump for all of Cleric Kind  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>-Cland</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana